{"id":"230912132_Tensor_completion_and_low-rank_tensor_recovery_via_convex_optimization","abstract":"In this paper we consider sparsity on a tensor level, as given by the n-rank of a tensor. In an important sparse-vector approximation problem (compressed sensing) and the low-rank matrix recovery problem, using a convex relaxation technique proved to be a valuable solution strategy. Here, we will adapt these techniques to the tensor setting. We use the n-rank of a tensor as a sparsity measure and consider the low-n-rank tensor recovery problem, i.e. the problem of finding the tensor of the lowest n-rank that fulfills some linear constraints. We introduce a tractable convex relaxation of the n-rank and propose efficient algorithms to solve the low-n-rank tensor recovery problem numerically. The algorithms are based on the Douglasâ€“Rachford splitting technique and its dual variant, the alternating direction method of multipliers.","authors":["Silvia Gandy","Benjamin Recht","Isao Yamada"],"meta":["January 2011Inverse Problems 27(2):025010","DOI:10.1088/0266-5611/27/2/025010"],"references":["228566525_Low_multilinear_rank_tensor_approximation_via_semidefinite_programming","226029783_On_the_Douglas-Rachford_splitting_method_and_the_proximal_point_algorithm_for_maximal_monotone_operators","224136132_Tensor_Completion_for_Estimating_Missing_Values_in_Visual_Data","1896344_Guaranteed_Minimum-Rank_Solutions_of_Linear_Matrix_Equations_via_Nuclear_Norm_Minimization","1749366_A_Proximal_Decomposition_Method_for_Solving_Convex_Variational_Inverse_Problems_Inverse_Problems_2427","342571583_Tensor_rank_is_NP-complete","285677677_Augmented_Lagrangian_Methods_Applications_to_the_Numerical_Solution_of_Boundary-Value_Problems","278762029_Signal_recovery_by_proximal_forwardC_backward_splitting","278282637_An_algorithm_for_total_variation_minimization_and_applications","269634033_Affine_Invariant_Flows_in_the_Beltrami_Framework","260365821_Sur_l'approximation_par_elements_finis_d'ordre_